FSRI: At approximately 90 seconds a candle sized flame ignited near the center of the sample, then extinguished a few seconds later. Ignition began at approximately 9 minutes as a candle sized flame at the edge of the sample, which slowly spread along the edges. The ignition event was recorded when the majority of the surface area was involved. By the time of ignition, the sample corners had slightly curled upwards, impacting the spark ignitor as it was removed and causing a spike in mass data.
